{"id": 13971, "source": "pestle", "subject": "biology", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "3", "year": "2019", "session": "19M", "subtopic": "c-4-conservation-of-biodiversity, c-5-population-ecology", "title": "19M.3.SL.TZ1.11", "topic_id": "c", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p>The table shows the distribution of four coral reef species along a transect as a function of depth.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"/></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[Source: © International Baccalaureate Organization 2019]</p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>From the data, identify the depth along the transect where the greatest species richness is observed.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Outline the relationship between <em>Zooxanthellae</em> and reef-building coral reef species.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Suggest <strong>one</strong> way in which depth may act as a limiting factor for coral. </p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>6.5 m ✔</p>\n<p><em>Unit required</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>a. a symbiotic/mutualistic relationship ✔</p>\n<p>b.<em> Zooxanthellae</em> obtain shelter/habitat/exposure to light ✔</p>\n<p>c. coral obtains energy/food through photosynthesis of the <em>Zooxanthellae</em> ✔</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>low light levels/lower temperatures cannot support growth/metabolism ✔</p>\n<p><em>Requires the explanation for the mark</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>Richness appeared well understood but the depth unit was sometimes omitted.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>This was a well-answered question with many candidates knowing the term symbiosis or mutualism. Protection provided by coral was often stated but the role of <em>Zooxanthellae</em> in providing nutrients from photosynthesis was less often seen.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>The reduction in light or temperature with greater depth was recognized but not often linked to growth or photosynthesis.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>"}